Instruction Selection[指令选取]
• Instruction selection is the stage of a compiler backend that 
transforms intermediate representation (IR) into a low-level IR.
• contains both instruction scheduling and register allocation.
• Its output IR may still be subject to peephole optimization[窥孔优化]. 
IR code (TAC):
a = b + c;
d = a + e;
Target code:
LD R0, b 
// R0 = b
ADD R0, R0, c 
// R0 = R0 + c
ST a, R0 
// a = R0
LD R0, a 
// R0 = a
ADD R0, R0, e 
// R0 = R0 + e
ST d, R0 
// d = R0
